How can a domain class play a part in many use cases?
It may have different roles in them or the same role.
It will always have the same role in them.
They always play a part in every use case.  They just do.
Each domain class represents the whole system, so by definition they do.
Correct. They can play different roles in different use cases.
Incorrect. They do not always have the same role in all use cases, they may have a differnt one or not play a role in some use cases at all.
Incorrect. They do not necessarily play the a part in every use case, they may only play a role in one.
Incorrect. Each domain class does not represent the whole system, they respresent a domain within the system and so can play a role in many use cases, but they could only play a role in one.

